## 1. Objective and Scope


### 1.1 Objective
The primary objective of this task is to enhance the user interface and user experience (UI/UX) flow for our member portal. This involves identifying friction points within the existing system and implementing improvements that facilitate ease of use, effectiveness, and user satisfaction—all while maintaining a focus on the healing-centric nature of our services.


### 1.2 Scope
This task will cover:
- Evaluation of the existing UI/UX flow as described in the file.
- Design and development of optimized interfaces.
- Harmonization with the FFPMA’s branding and user engagement philosophies.
- Integration of nature-inspired design elements into the digital experience.


---


## 2. Current State Assessment


### 2.1 Analysis of Current Interface
A thorough analysis will be conducted on the existing UI/UX flow to determine:
- User pain points and accessibility challenges.
- Alignment with FFPMA's healing mission and aesthetics.
- Areas where the user journey can be streamlined.


### 2.2 Tools and Metrics for Evaluation
Utilize tools such as heatmaps, user feedback surveys, and interaction analytics to gather data on user behavior and identify opportunities for improvement.


